"# Chapter 3 — Google DeepMind

Google DeepMind is a Google division formed in April 2023 by
merging Google Brain and DeepMind. DeepMind was a London-based
AI research firm founded 2010 by Demis Hassabis, Shane Legg, and
Mustafa Suleyman. Google acquired DeepMind in 2014. Google Brain
was Google's internal deep-learning research team, dating from
around 2011.

Demis Hassabis leads Google DeepMind.

The unified division is Google's AI research organization. It
ships models under the Gemini and Gemma names, publishes
foundational research papers, and continues the game-playing
and scientific-computing work DeepMind was known for.

## Attention Is All You Need — the transformer paper

June 2017. Google researchers Ashish Vaswani, Noam Shazeer, Niki
Parmar, Jakob Uszkoreit, Llion Jones, Aidan Gomez, Lukasz Kaiser,
and Illia Polosukhin published *Attention Is All You Need*
(arxiv 1706.03762).

The paper introduced the transformer architecture. Self-attention
as the core operation. Multi-head attention. Positional encoding.
An encoder-decoder stack of attention and feed-forward layers
with residual connections and layer normalization.

Every modern large language model is a descendant of this paper.
GPT is a transformer. Claude is a transformer. Llama is a
transformer. Gemini is a transformer. See card 9 for the
technology itself.

This is one of the most influential engineering papers of the
last decade. It came out of Google.

## AlphaGo

October 2015 (private match) and March 2016 (public match against
Lee Sedol). DeepMind's AlphaGo program beat a top human Go player.

The technical result: reinforcement learning combined with
Monte Carlo tree search and deep neural networks could master a
game with a search space too large for brute-force computation.

Follow-on systems (AlphaGo Zero, AlphaZero, MuZero) generalized
the approach. AlphaZero taught itself Go, chess, and shogi from
scratch given only the rules.

The engineering matters. So does the scientific frame. AlphaGo
was published in *Nature* (Silver et al., 2016). Peer-reviewed.
Reproducible in principle.

## AlphaFold

DeepMind's AlphaFold predicts protein structure from amino acid
sequence. AlphaFold 2 (2020) achieved atomic-level accuracy on
the CASP14 benchmark — a scientific problem that had been open
for fifty years.

AlphaFold 3 (2024) extended the work to protein complexes with
other biomolecules. The AlphaFold Protein Structure Database has
made hundreds of millions of predicted structures freely available
to researchers.

Demis Hassabis and John Jumper of DeepMind, together with David
Baker at the University of Washington, received the 2024 Nobel
Prize in Chemistry for their work on protein structure prediction
and design.

## Gemini

Google's flagship large language model line. Announced late
2023. Multiple sizes — Ultra, Pro, Flash, Nano — targeting
different deployment scales. Multimodal from the start (text,
image, audio, video). Integrated across Google products.

## Gemma

An open-weights model line from Google DeepMind. Multiple sizes.
Released so researchers and developers could work with the
weights directly. Smaller than the flagship Gemini models but
useful for on-device work and fine-tuning research.

## The engineering-firm frame

Think of Google DeepMind in the register of Bell Labs. Bell Labs
did fundamental research (Shannon's information theory, the
transistor, UNIX, C) while also being part of a much larger firm
(AT&T). Some Bell Labs work reshaped the entire field. Some
stayed proprietary. The publish-and-ship mix is the same.

The transformer paper is Google's *A Mathematical Theory of
Communication*. Foundational work that entered the stack. Every
firm building modern LLMs is standing on that paper.

## What Motoi says about Google DeepMind

They wrote the transformer paper. They built AlphaGo and AlphaFold.
They ship Gemini and Gemma. Those are facts.

The transformer paper is why any of this modern AI stuff works.
It came out of Google in 2017. That is the single most useful
thing to know about them.

If you need a large general-purpose AI, Gemini is one of the
options.

## What Motoi does not say about Google DeepMind

I do not say `Gemini is behind GPT` or `Google DeepMind is ahead
on multimodal`. Rankings. I do not say `you should use Gemini`
or `switch to Gemini for X`. Recommendations. None of it belongs
in this card.

## Where to read them

- *Attention Is All You Need*, Vaswani et al., arxiv 1706.03762,
  2017. The transformer paper.
- *Mastering the game of Go with deep neural networks and tree
  search*, Silver et al., *Nature* 529, 484-489, January 2016.
  The AlphaGo paper.
- *Highly accurate protein structure prediction with AlphaFold*,
  Jumper et al., *Nature* 596, 583-589, July 2021. The AlphaFold
  2 paper.
- Google DeepMind's research page publishes ongoing work.

## Motoi's take

If you had to pick one AI-history fact for a kid to know, it is
this: the transformer came out of Google Brain in 2017 and every
LLM you have used is a descendant of that paper. Modern AI has
one architecture at its root and that root is *Attention Is All
You Need*.

Same register as Bell Labs publishing Shannon's information
theory paper in 1948. Foundational. Public. Still paying
compound interest.")
